		<h1 class="pageTitle">About</h1>
		VDrift is a cross-platform, open source driving simulation made with drift racing in mind. The driving physics engine was recently re-written from scratch but was inspired and owes much to the <a href="http://vamos.sourceforge.net">Vamos physics engine</a>. It is released under the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html">GNU General Public License (GPL) v2</a>. It is currently available for <a href="http://www.linux.org/">Linux</a>, <a href="http://www.freebsd.org/">FreeBSD</a>, <a href="http://www.apple.com/macosx/">Mac OS X</a> and Windows. <br /><br /> This game is in the early stages of development but is already very playable. Currently the game features:
            <ul>
                <li>Simulation-grade driving physics</li>
                <li>Tracks based on famous real-world tracks</li>
                <li>Cars based on real-world vehicles</li>
                <li>Competition against AI players</li>
                <li>Mouse/joystick/gamepad/wheel/keyboard support</li>
                <li><a href="http://wiki.vdrift.net/About_the_project">More...</a></li>
            </ul>
